  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Indexed\nfolder 01 - 042}\n541\n\nBut what I would stress at this point is that the Form world when it broke into the world of accidents (or I ascended to it, as Plotinus describes) --it was so vast; the spaces were enormous; it was so much more real, awesome, than the epiphenomenal world that we normally go through our lives experiencing. I would say, Yes, it did seem like an archetypal world, in both the Platonist sense and the Jungian sense; it was immense in terms of substance, of space, of time",
      "matched_alias": "Jungian",
      "term_id": "TERM_jungian",
      "term_name": "Jungian",
      "term_slug": "jungian"
    },
